### **Toggle Script**

```javascript
// simple light ↔ dark switch
const btn = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
  const light = document.getElementById('lightTheme');
  const dark = document.getElementById('darkTheme');

  const darkIsOn = !dark.disabled;
  if (darkIsOn) {
    dark.disabled = true;
    light.disabled = false;
    btn.textContent = '🌙 Switch Theme';
  } else {
    dark.disabled = false;
    light.disabled = true;
    btn.textContent = '☀️ Switch Theme';
  }
});
```

---

### **Automatic preference**

If you’d rather let the visitor’s system decide, skip the button and use this CSS line in the *light* file:

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  @import url("supportive-flow-dark.css");
}
```

That way the page adapts automatically to their OS dark/light setting.

---

